Within-subject (20/24 papers, 83%) is the most utilized methodology among the literature papers. The average number of participants is 21 ± SD 12.9, with a minimum age of 18 and a maximum age of 50. Most are right-handed (92%), young (SD 3.1, mean 25.8), and male (65%) (**FIGURE 37**). The majority are student participants (90%), some unpaid volunteers (4/24 papers), and some paid (4/24 papers), while the rest is not specified.

